You'll be asleep
before the first day

16:05.834 --> 16:07.531
of this circus is over.

16:07.575 --> 16:09.533
Oh, and by the way,

16:09.577 --> 16:11.796
guess who's gonna be getting
the morning slot?

16:15.583 --> 16:16.714
Rick Weider.

16:16.758 --> 16:18.038
Let me ask you
something.

16:18.064 --> 16:20.153
Oh, hey.
Uh, thanks for calling back.

16:20.196 --> 16:21.869
Let me, uh, let me get
your name and number

16:21.893 --> 16:23.547
in case
we get disconnected again.

16:23.591 --> 16:25.723
You are going to reach
for something.

16:25.767 --> 16:27.856
- Right, Rick?
- Yeah, man, I'm reaching.

16:27.899 --> 16:30.163
You, uh, you mentioned
the doctor before.

16:30.206 --> 16:31.705
- The doctor that...
- You've got to give them

16:31.729 --> 16:34.167
more substance than sensation.

16:34.210 --> 16:37.909
Honestly convey your passion to your listeners.

16:37.953 --> 16:39.365
Uh-huh. You're right.
The human element.

16:39.389 --> 16:41.565
So with you. So, tell me, you...

16:41.609 --> 16:43.785
Stop yessing me,
Weider!

16:43.828 --> 16:46.614
You're not expecting enough
from your listeners!

16:46.657 --> 16:48.355
You have no idea
what they're capable of

16:48.398 --> 16:49.965
if they can believe in you.

16:50.009 --> 16:51.967
Be real! Be honest!

16:52.011 --> 16:55.057
They will rise up in solidarity with our cause,

16:55.101 --> 16:57.016
and we will triumph!

16:57.059 --> 17:00.062
Do not blow this!

17:01.455 --> 17:02.673
Dude.

17:02.717 --> 17:04.240
What the hell was that?

17:04.284 --> 17:07.113
Ah, he was just a prank caller.

17:07.156 --> 17:09.202
I take back what I said.

17:09.244 --> 17:11.030
This will be over by lunch.

17:15.817 --> 17:17.426
Rick. Rick?

17:18.689 --> 17:19.907
Rick!

17:19.951 --> 17:22.084
Um, this is Dr. Gray,
the SMA expert.

17:24.130 --> 17:25.131
Hello, doctor.

17:25.740 --> 17:27.436
Welcome.

17:27.481 --> 17:31.528
I'm moving out of SMA
into other fields of research.

17:31.572 --> 17:32.660
Oh.

17:32.703 --> 17:34.009
Oh, that's a shame.

17:34.053 --> 17:35.880
Joining me once again
is Dr. Gray,

17:35.924 --> 17:38.448
who has been illuminating us
on the subject of SMA.

17:38.492 --> 17:40.015
So, Dr. Gray,

17:40.059 --> 17:41.799
tell us more about the,

17:41.843 --> 17:45.716
the challenges of dealing
with this deadly disease.

17:45.760 --> 17:49.764
The families must face
difficult lifestyle decisions,

17:49.807 --> 17:52.288
uh, in order to make life
manageable

17:52.332 --> 17:54.725
for their children, and...

17:54.769 --> 17:59.034
of course, the specter of death
is always a burden to bear.

17:59.078 --> 18:00.122
Intricate stuff.

18:00.166 --> 18:02.472
Prognosis is tricky.

18:03.212 --> 18:04.735
Time-cost issues,

18:04.779 --> 18:06.041
parental expectations...

18:06.085 --> 18:08.304
For, for tangible results.

18:08.348 --> 18:10.132
Ta... Tangible results?

18:10.176 --> 18:11.699
To save a life.

18:11.742 --> 18:13.440
We need to find a cure.

18:13.483 --> 18:16.138
Uh, and you think Dr. Rance
was making headway?

18:16.182 --> 18:18.184
I mean, he died so suddenly.

18:18.227 --> 18:22.362
Were, were you working with him
toward that tangible result?

18:22.405 --> 18:23.841
That's a...

18:25.191 --> 18:27.018
That's difficult to go...

18:27.671 --> 18:29.151
...to go into.

18:35.375 --> 18:37.681
Oh, uh, we'll...
we'll be right back.

18:37.725 --> 18:40.119
I'm terribly sorry.

18:40.162 --> 18:41.424
I'm terribly sorry.

18:41.468 --> 18:43.731
Don't worry, man.
It's radio. No one saw it.

18:43.774 --> 18:45.317
Yeah, um...

18:45.341 --> 18:46.386
I've, uh...

18:46.429 --> 18:48.083
I've been under...

18:48.127 --> 18:49.998
tremendous stress.

18:50.041 --> 18:52.043
- Pharmacy is two blocks down.
- Oh, okay.

18:52.087 --> 18:53.697
I've, uh...

18:53.741 --> 18:55.482
I've been getting these...

18:55.525 --> 18:57.092
these terrible threats.

19:07.233 --> 19:09.539
That was... disgusting.

19:09.583 --> 19:11.498
Smile. It's for charity.

19:14.370 --> 19:16.067
WZLW Rick Weider.

19:16.111 --> 19:17.895
"Tangible result"?

19:17.939 --> 19:21.856
I'll give you a tangible result.

19:21.899 --> 19:23.225
He doesn't look healthy enough-It's that guy.

19:23.249 --> 19:24.598
to live anyway.

19:24.641 --> 19:26.382
- What?
- Yeah.

19:27.514 --> 19:30.125
You see him now?

19:30.169 --> 19:33.520
He definitely doesn't look like he's gonna make it.

19:33.563 --> 19:35.870
You gonna threaten
one of my guests now?

19:35.913 --> 19:38.307
Call this a lesson
in dedication.

19:38.351 --> 19:41.267
You're not gonna do anything.

19:41.310 --> 19:44.183
You're just another media-crazy,
celebrity ballbuster.

19:44.226 --> 19:46.620
- Get a life.
- Like Gray's?

19:46.663 --> 19:49.188
And when I'm finished
busting, Rick,

19:50.363 --> 19:52.147
you'll be a star.

19:53.017 --> 19:54.105
Go find Gray. Now.

19:54.149 --> 19:55.498
- Okay?
- What?

19:55.542 --> 19:56.649
- He's going to the pharmacy. Go!
- What's going on?

19:56.673 --> 19:58.109
Just please!

19:58.153 --> 19:59.565
- Tell me what's going on.
- Please go find Gray now!

19:59.589 --> 20:01.200
Go! Go!

20:03.114 --> 20:04.377
Okay, jokes over.

20:04.420 --> 20:06.030
Knock it off,
or I'm calling the police.

20:06.074 --> 20:08.598
Better call the morgue.

20:13.081 --> 20:14.778
Charlene, do you see him?

20:14.822 --> 20:16.780
Not yet. What's going on?

20:16.824 --> 20:18.652
Wait, look.

20:18.695 --> 20:20.001
I don't know what you're after,

20:20.044 --> 20:22.656
but this isn't helping
your kid, okay?

20:22.699 --> 20:24.048
Look, you hear me?

20:24.092 --> 20:25.136
I said this isn't helping.

20:25.180 --> 20:26.573
She died.

20:27.878 --> 20:29.228
She died.

20:32.796 --> 20:34.929
Charlene, what's happening?

20:34.972 --> 20:36.496
I'm looking.

20:36.539 --> 20:38.019
Come on, Charlene.
Give me something.

20:38.062 --> 20:39.716
Uh, yeah.
Excuse me, excuse me.

20:44.460 --> 20:46.680
Oh, god, Rick.

20:46.723 --> 20:47.898
Oh, god.

20:47.942 --> 20:49.204
No.

20:49.248 --> 20:51.598
He's... He's dead, Rick.
He's dead!

20:52.903 --> 20:54.818
He's dead.

20:54.862 --> 20:57.560
He's dead!

21:15.012 --> 21:16.405
Message received?

21:17.885 --> 21:19.669
You killed him?

21:19.713 --> 21:23.107
You killed him for a radio show?

21:23.151 --> 21:25.371
Five million.

21:25.414 --> 21:28.504
You're going to raise
five million dollars

21:28.548 --> 21:30.419
before you fall asleep.

21:31.681 --> 21:33.901
Not 20,000.

21:33.944 --> 21:36.338
Not a hundred thousand.

21:36.382 --> 21:38.427
Five million dollars,

21:38.471 --> 21:40.081
or you're next.

21:40.690 --> 21:42.866
You're insane.

21:42.910 --> 21:45.521
Five million dollars
before you sleep.

21:47.218 --> 21:49.220
Or you will never...

21:49.786 --> 21:51.005
wake up.

21:53.703 --> 21:54.704
Wait.

21:55.618 --> 21:57.620
Wait, that's impossible.

21:57.664 --> 21:59.274
It, it can't be done.

22:17.423 --> 22:18.815
Look, Rick, you can't...

22:18.859 --> 22:21.470
You can't stay awake
until we raise five million...

22:21.514 --> 22:22.602
Five million.

22:22.645 --> 22:24.386
What am I gonna do, huh?

22:24.430 --> 22:25.798
If I fall asleep,
he's gonna kill me.

22:25.822 --> 22:26.997
I have to break the record.

22:27.041 --> 22:28.912
Okay, okay.
Say that you do break it...

22:28.956 --> 22:30.412
...there's no guarantee

22:30.436 --> 22:32.263
you're gonna raise
that much money.

22:32.307 --> 22:35.179
I mean, it's not even possible
to go 11 days.

22:35.223 --> 22:36.746
No? Tell her, Falco. Tell her.

22:36.790 --> 22:39.140
But if you could
get past 11 days

22:39.183 --> 22:40.620
and break the record,

22:40.663 --> 22:44.014
the research data alone
would be invaluable.

22:44.058 --> 22:45.581
Research data. Great.

22:47.191 --> 22:48.454
Shit.

22:50.020 --> 22:51.326
Nice cage.

22:52.762 --> 22:55.243
But your ratings,
they haven't improved, and...

22:55.286 --> 22:56.505
you've got a dead guest.

22:57.985 --> 22:59.421
You really think
you're gonna raise

22:59.465 --> 23:01.467
five million dollars
with this sideshow?

23:02.468 --> 23:03.512
Do you?

23:03.556 --> 23:06.167
Money will pour in. You'll see.

23:06.210 --> 23:07.516
All right.

23:07.560 --> 23:08.691
Of course, it will.

23:15.219 --> 23:18.005
♪ And I love you

23:18.048 --> 23:20.703
WZLW. Good morning!

23:20.747 --> 23:24.620
Day two
of the great Wake-A-Thon.

23:24.664 --> 23:28.624
We, uh, we had, uh,
an exciting show yesterday.

23:28.668 --> 23:30.147
Emotions ran high.

23:30.191 --> 23:33.934
And, uh, the city was dared
to raise the bar

23:33.977 --> 23:37.416
to five million dollars.

23:38.591 --> 23:39.698
So, let's jump it,
New York.

23:39.722 --> 23:41.594
Help alleviate
a child's suffering.

23:43.639 --> 23:45.075
Make your pledges now.

23:46.555 --> 23:49.166
♪ A blessing from heaven

23:50.254 --> 23:52.561
♪ I'm so grateful

23:54.520 --> 23:57.392
♪ For this love that I found

24:02.397 --> 24:04.051
Wake up, son!

24:04.094 --> 24:06.401
Wake up for life.

24:06.445 --> 24:09.273
Please don't give up now.

24:09.317 --> 24:14.061
♪ Gets stuck
Between the stations ♪

24:15.236 --> 24:19.370
♪ Then just move that antenna

24:21.938 --> 24:25.768
♪ Until you tune me back in

24:56.320 --> 24:58.888
♪ I loved you

25:02.849 --> 25:06.026
♪ For you who thought I was

25:11.510 --> 25:12.946
♪ Now I'm

25:14.513 --> 25:16.558
♪ Leaving you, baby

25:16.602 --> 25:20.388
♪ Because all your friends

25:20.431 --> 25:21.650
♪ They say

25:21.694 --> 25:24.784
♪ They might like
What they see ♪

25:24.827 --> 25:28.309
♪ But I can't go on
Livin' my life ♪

25:33.096 --> 25:34.315
♪ Livin' my life

25:35.708 --> 25:38.624
♪ Through your vision of me

25:45.413 --> 25:47.850
Rick Weider.

25:47.894 --> 25:50.331
You're not telling
the dollar amounts.

25:50.374 --> 25:51.854
How much have you raised?

25:53.813 --> 25:55.249
Uh...

25:55.945 --> 25:56.990
So...

25:58.252 --> 26:00.733
What do I call you?

26:00.776 --> 26:02.822
We started this
with a quote

26:02.865 --> 26:04.301
from Robert Browning.

26:05.215 --> 26:06.390
Leave it at that.

26:08.654 --> 26:10.873
Okay. Okay, Browning.

26:12.875 --> 26:13.920
Browning.

26:15.312 --> 26:16.836
Do you think Dr. Gray
was wondering,

26:16.879 --> 26:18.272
"What's a heaven for?"

26:18.315 --> 26:20.796
Gray was a selfish
little sponge

26:20.840 --> 26:23.407
soaking up perks
from the drug companies.

26:24.713 --> 26:27.281
I have bigger plans
for you, Rick.

26:27.324 --> 26:29.326
You want me to be real
for my audience, huh?

26:30.284 --> 26:33.113
Why don't you be real with them?

26:33.156 --> 26:35.898
Come on the show,
and, uh, tell us your story.

26:35.942 --> 26:39.032
Inspire us with your dedication
that killed doctors

26:39.075 --> 26:40.773
to make them find a cure faster

26:40.816 --> 26:42.992
or whatever the hell it is
you're doing.

26:43.036 --> 26:44.777
Five million dollars

26:44.820 --> 26:46.430
before you sleep.

26:46.474 --> 26:48.781
Hey, look, look, look, Browning.

26:48.824 --> 26:52.872
Um, your, your daughter died,
and...

26:52.915 --> 26:54.743
and now you wanna help others.

26:54.787 --> 26:57.659
I, I get that, but...

26:57.703 --> 27:00.575
Rick. Rick! You're on!

27:00.619 --> 27:02.403
Rick, you're on.

27:02.838 --> 27:04.100
Oh.

27:06.537 --> 27:08.714
All right,
this is The Rick Weider Show,

27:08.757 --> 27:12.413
and we're rocking
to find a cure for SMA,

27:12.456 --> 27:14.241
and, uh, and to stay awake.

27:19.420 --> 27:20.856
Are you okay?

27:25.731 --> 27:28.342
I've been trying to get you
for two days.

27:29.430 --> 27:30.997
Detective Murdoch.

27:31.040 --> 27:33.564
Your killer
just threatened me again.

27:33.608 --> 27:37.830
To, to murder me if, if I don't
raise millions before I sleep.

27:37.873 --> 27:39.353
A murderer? Oh.

27:40.659 --> 27:42.704
That's a great hook.

27:42.748 --> 27:44.750
Grab your audience,
reel 'em in.

27:44.793 --> 27:45.968
Hey, hey, hey.

27:47.187 --> 27:50.103
Do I look
like I'm making this up?

27:51.452 --> 27:53.193
Why would someone
wanna kill the doctor?

27:53.236 --> 27:55.325
I don't know.
How the hell should I know?

27:55.369 --> 27:57.066
Um, maybe, maybe, uh...

27:57.110 --> 27:59.634
Maybe he knew too much.

28:00.809 --> 28:01.810
About what?

28:02.811 --> 28:04.160
About him.

28:04.204 --> 28:05.858
Him, the files.
Files or something.

28:05.901 --> 28:07.598
Files, files that...

28:07.642 --> 28:09.644
can link him
to the first murder,

28:09.688 --> 28:11.254
and so, he kills him.

28:11.298 --> 28:12.603
With a poisoned syringe?

28:14.780 --> 28:16.477
The first doctor
had his intestines

28:16.520 --> 28:17.913
hanging over the East River.

28:19.698 --> 28:21.569
That's an entirely different MO.

28:21.612 --> 28:24.267
So what?

28:24.311 --> 28:26.748
How many phone calls
did you receive from this, um,

28:26.792 --> 28:27.836
supposed killer?

28:28.489 --> 28:30.012
Um...

28:30.056 --> 28:31.163
I don't know, three?

28:31.187 --> 28:32.275
No. No, four.

28:32.319 --> 28:34.234
When was the first call?

28:34.277 --> 28:37.324
About, uh... About a week ago.

28:37.367 --> 28:39.848
When did he reveal to you
that he killed the first doctor?

28:40.675 --> 28:42.024
The first call...

28:42.068 --> 28:44.331
So you knew days ahead
of this, this Wake-A-Thon

28:44.374 --> 28:46.463
that this guy was the killer.

28:46.507 --> 28:47.963
I might have tried
to reel him in myself,

28:47.987 --> 28:49.510
and that was stupid.

28:49.553 --> 28:51.164
Stupid.

28:51.207 --> 28:53.906
And now he's...
He's killed Gray,

28:53.949 --> 28:55.734
and he's set on killing me.

28:56.822 --> 28:58.954
That is not a hoax.

28:58.998 --> 29:00.651
So you've gotta do something.

29:00.695 --> 29:03.437
Police work isn't done
in front of your microphone.

29:04.699 --> 29:06.570
For the last two days,

29:06.614 --> 29:08.529
I've taken statements
from his associates,

29:08.572 --> 29:10.836
searched their offices.

29:10.879 --> 29:13.664
I even had an autopsy done
on Dr. Gray.

29:14.665 --> 29:15.841
He died...

29:17.364 --> 29:18.974
of a heart attack.

29:19.018 --> 29:20.454
A heart attack? No.

29:22.935 --> 29:24.458
For SMA.

29:24.501 --> 29:25.546
Have a nice day.

29:36.513 --> 29:37.906
Rick?

30:08.632 --> 30:10.896
Psst. Rick.

30:10.939 --> 30:12.636
Ricky boy.

30:12.680 --> 30:14.595
Oh, Rick.

30:14.638 --> 30:16.336
From your throat...

30:16.379 --> 30:19.252
Rick. Rick.
Oh, Ricky boy.

30:19.295 --> 30:20.470
Oh, Rick.

30:20.906 --> 30:22.211
Hey.

30:22.255 --> 30:23.299
Down here.

30:24.300 --> 30:25.606
Hi, pal.

30:25.649 --> 30:28.217
Wow, you certainly
look like hell.

30:28.261 --> 30:29.716
You don't really think
you're going to break

30:29.740 --> 30:31.264
the record, do you?

30:31.307 --> 30:33.875
Eleven days.
That would be something.

30:33.919 --> 30:35.659
You're a loser, though.

30:35.703 --> 30:36.965
So, no chance.

30:37.009 --> 30:38.445
Hey, guess what?

30:38.488 --> 30:41.361
I've got a hot date
with your wife tonight.

30:41.404 --> 30:43.711
I mean, with you
being such a dud,

30:43.754 --> 30:46.627
she'll come running
into my big beautiful arms.

30:46.670 --> 30:48.368
"Mantis, love."

30:48.411 --> 30:49.562
- Stop talking to me, okay?
- Ooh.

30:49.586 --> 30:50.868
- Stop talking to me.
- She's going to...

30:50.892 --> 30:52.043
- Stop talking to me, okay?
- love it, love it.

30:52.067 --> 30:53.112
Love it!

30:53.155 --> 30:54.504
- Shut up.
- Hey.

30:54.548 --> 30:56.221
Do you see that, chap?
What's he doing out there?

30:56.245 --> 30:57.507
- What?
- Strange.

31:34.022 --> 31:35.565
Hey, this is Kathy.

31:35.589 --> 31:36.938
Leave a message.

31:36.982 --> 31:38.026
Kathy.

31:39.898 --> 31:41.116
Darling, you're...

31:43.205 --> 31:44.859
You're my bride,
and you're the...

31:44.903 --> 31:46.382
You're the most important thing

31:46.426 --> 31:47.862
in the world to me. It's...

31:52.084 --> 31:53.999
I'm not gonna let anything...

31:55.000 --> 31:56.740
come between us.

31:56.784 --> 31:59.004
I'm not, I'm not going anywhere.

32:00.309 --> 32:02.790
I'm just,
I'm just sitting here, uh...

32:04.183 --> 32:05.619
hoping that...

32:23.376 --> 32:24.377
Rick Weider.

32:25.291 --> 32:26.945
I miss her.

32:28.294 --> 32:30.557
I miss my little girl.

32:31.688 --> 32:34.126
How'd you find my cell number?

32:34.169 --> 32:35.910
It's not that hard.

32:36.824 --> 32:39.044
Smart guy, huh?

32:39.087 --> 32:41.611
You can make a murder
look like a heart attack, too.

32:41.655 --> 32:43.048
Necessity,

32:43.091 --> 32:44.701
mother of invention.

32:44.745 --> 32:47.008
You're a loser, Weider.

32:47.052 --> 32:48.314
I popped by earlier.

32:49.445 --> 32:50.838
You sounded terrible,

32:50.881 --> 32:53.275
so I figured I should check
on my investment.

32:53.928 --> 32:55.147
How old was she?

32:57.801 --> 32:59.020
I said,

32:59.064 --> 33:02.154
how old was your daughter
when she died?

33:02.197 --> 33:04.156
I don't wanna talk
about her,

33:04.199 --> 33:05.809
- circus boy.
- What was her name?

33:05.853 --> 33:07.507
None of your business!

33:07.550 --> 33:09.683
You gotta give me
something, okay?

33:09.726 --> 33:11.424
People are telling me
you're a hoax.

33:11.467 --> 33:13.227
- You know better.
- I know squat!

33:14.035 --> 33:15.689
I just, I just...

33:15.732 --> 33:17.691
I need a human face, man.

33:17.734 --> 33:19.954
She's not your poster child.

33:19.998 --> 33:22.087
What's the investment for?

33:22.130 --> 33:23.325
Who are we fighting for?

33:23.349 --> 33:25.351
Who are we fighting for?

33:25.394 --> 33:27.005
Who are we fighting for?

33:28.049 --> 33:29.311
Clarissa.

33:31.444 --> 33:32.749
Got you, you bastard.

33:32.793 --> 33:34.490
- What the hell's going on?
- Clarissa.

33:34.534 --> 33:36.144
Her name is Clarissa.

33:36.188 --> 33:37.363
Clarissa?

33:37.406 --> 33:40.105
I need to speak
to Detective Murdoch.

33:40.148 --> 33:41.367
This is an emergency.

33:45.110 --> 33:46.633
All right.

33:46.676 --> 33:49.027
What is this, this emergency
you're going on about?

33:49.070 --> 33:50.221
What? Are you having
a heart attack, too?

